<figureCitation box="[159,244,1445,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="64.[151,255,1879,1903]" captionTargetBox="[273,1314,198,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-84@64.[272,1320,194,1845]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 29. Photos and SEMs of chaetae of Neomicrorbis azoricus. Azores, 37°18'N 24°45.5'W, 610 m, R/V “Jean Charcot”, det. and don. H. Zibrowius, ZMA V.Pol. 3905. A—Lateral view of entire animal removed from its tube (photo R. Bastida-Zavala), B—operculum (photo R. Bastida-Zavala), C—tube (photo H. Zibrowius), D—anterior abdominal uncini, E—4th thoracic bundle of thin “capillary” and Apomatus chaetae, F—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
